WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified display profile for Micro-LED emissive display technology.
It defines the self-emissive inorganic semiconductor structure (GaN for
blue/green, AlInGaP for red), sub-nanosecond response time, extreme
luminance linearity, wide color gamut, and scalability from small
wearable panels to large video walls. This is the canonical reference
for GIOP ODTs targeting Micro-LED displays.

WHY IT EXISTS
Micro-LED is emerging as the ultimate emissive display technology, with
response times orders of magnitude faster than OLED and luminance
capability far beyond LCD. An ODT for Micro-LED must know its true
luminance linearity (no roll-off) and its ability to sustain high
brightness indefinitely without burn-in. This file provides the
physics-based model for next-generation mastering and consumer displays.

HOW IT WORKS
This file specifies:
  1. Semiconductor materials and emission wavelengths.
  2. Sub-nanosecond response time and its impact on motion resolution.
  3. Luminance linearity and dynamic range.
  4. Color primaries and gamut coverage.
  5. Scalability and pixel pitch.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Future cinema mastering monitors
- Large-scale LED video walls (virtual production)
- Consumer TVs and smartwatches
- Augmented reality glasses.

WHO USES IT
- L1 Architects: designing new display standards.
